anings":["Biblical name, borne by the greatest of all the kings of Israel, whose history is recounted with great vividness in the first and second books of Samuel and elsewhere. As a boy he killed the giant Philistine Goliath with his slingshot. As king of Judah, and later of all Israel, he expanded the power of the Israelites and established the security of their kingdom. He was also noted as a poet, many of the Psalms being attributed to him. The Hebrew derivation of the name is uncertain; it is said by some to represent a nursery word meaning ‘darling’. It is a very popular Jewish name, but is almost equally common among Gentiles in the English-speaking world. It is particularly common in Wales and Scotland, having been borne by the patron saint of Wales (  see  Dewi   ) and by two medieval kings of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir David Torthorwald was born in 1340, in Dumfriesshire, Scotland. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1340–Deceased":"1340–Surnud","1375–Female":"1375–Surnud","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1340–Deceased":"1340–Kuollut","1375–Female":"1375–Kuollut","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1340–Deceased":"1340–Décédé","1375–Female":"1375–Décédée","1340–Male":"1340–Décédé","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Sir David Torthorwald est né en 1340, à Dumfriesshire, Écosse. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1340–Deceased":"1340–Verstorben","1375–Female":"1375–Verstorben","1340–Male":"1340–Verstorben","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Sir David Torthorwald wurde 1340 in Dumfriesshire, Scotland geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"1340–Deceased":"1340–Desede","1375–Female":"1375–Desede","1340–Male":"1340–Desede","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","Dumfrie